  "texts": [
    "Formative feedback may also include different types of information such as cognitive (organizing elements of task requirements, elaboration of content), metacognitive (e.g., monitoring and self-regulation) or motivational aspects (e.g., relevance of addressing the task) (Candel et al., 2020).",
    "Cognitively activating activities are tasks that stimulate students' cognitive processes (C. Förtsch et al., 2017; Hofer et al., 1175).",
    "These processes include problem-solving, critical thinking, and understand-ing (Groß-Mlynek et al., 2022).",
    "The goal of these activities is to engage students' minds in a way that promotes active learning and encourages them to think deeply about the material (C. Förtsch et al., 2017).",
    "In physics, Hofer et al (Hofer et al., 1175) have devised cognitively stimulating instructions to aid in the acquisition of a robust base of conceptual knowledge."
  ],
